  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-03-09",
    "date": "2007-04-24T21:38:25Z",
    "text": "Consumer Fairness Act of 2007 - Amends the Consumer Credit Protection Act to treat as an unfair and deceptive trade act or practice under federal or state law any written provision in a consumer transaction or contract which requires binding arbitration to resolve a controversy arising out of or related to the transaction or contract, or the failure to perform any part.\n\nDeclares such a provision unenforceable.\n\nPermits a written agreement to determine an existing controversy by binding arbitration if the parties agree after the controversy has arisen."
  },
